===Alternative forms===
* [[æquinox]] {{i|chiefly archaic}}

===Etymology===
From Latin {{term|aequus||equal|lang=la}} + {{term|nox||night|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|/'ɛkwɪˌnoks/|/ˈiːkwɪˌnɒks/}}, {{SAMPA|/"i:kw@%nQks/}}
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|/ˈiːkwəˌnɑːks/}}, {{SAMPA|/"i:kw@%nA:ks/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|equinoxes|pl2=equinoctes}}

# The [[intersection]] of the [[ecliptic]] (apparent path of the sun) with the [[celestial]] [[equator]]. ''Vernal Equinox'' is the intersection that the [[sun]] crosses about March 20; ''autumnal equinox'' denotes the crossing point about September 23.

